  "title": "Site Engineer & PE Assignee",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Plan and schedule work in accordance to the master and detailed work programme</li>\n  <li>Liaise with Professional Engineer on the Temporary works</li>\n  <li>Liaise with consultants (QPS) for technical issues and coordinate site activities with subcontractors</li>\n  <li>Handle technical and engineering problems</li>\n  <li>Provide guidance to supervisors in relation to construction works and ensure work progress according to schedule</li>\n  <li>Maintain quality standards, carry out site inspections and resolve technical issues on time</li>\n  <li>Prepare report and method statement whenever necessary</li>\n  <li>Manage workers and monitor their work closely to keep site safe and neat</li>\n  <li>Supervise ongoing site activities closely</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree in Civil Engineering recognised by Singapore PE Board</li>\n  <li>Registered Resident Engineer with IES/BCA with valid certification in Singapore</li>\n  <li>At least 1 years' working experience in Singapore</li>\n  <li>Experienced as a PE assignee for standing supervision of works, preferably with LTA projects.</li>\n  <li>Ability to communicate well with project principal and subcontractors</li>\n  <li>Able to commit to long work hours to meet tight project deadlines</li>\n</ul>",
